## Example `api/.htaccess` for LetShare
## This is a template â€” do NOT put secrets here. Adjust the CORS origin and rules for your deployment.

# Allow CORS from your frontend host (replace example.com)
<IfModule mod_headers.c>
    Header set Access-Control-Allow-Origin "https://example.com"
    Header set Access-Control-Allow-Methods "GET, POST, OPTIONS"
    Header set Access-Control-Allow-Headers "Content-Type, Authorization"
    Header set Access-Control-Allow-Credentials true
</IfModule>

# Security headers (adjust as needed)
<IfModule mod_headers.c>
    Header always set X-Frame-Options "SAMEORIGIN"
    Header always set X-Content-Type-Options "nosniff"
    Header always set Referrer-Policy "no-referrer-when-downgrade"
    Header always set X-XSS-Protection "1; mode=block"
</IfModule>

# Deny direct access to sensitive config files (example)
<FilesMatch "^(config\.php|\.env)$">
    Require all denied
</FilesMatch>

# If you need environment-specific overrides, use an `api/.htaccess.local` not committed to git.
